Supplies.Name: Splintered scutum
Supplies.Description: The scutum is a 10 kg large rectangle curved shield made from three sheets of wood glued together and covered with canvas and leather, usually with a spindle shaped boss along the vertical length of the shield. The scutum is light enough to be held in one hand and its large height and width cover the entire soldier, making him very unlikely to be hit by missile fire and in hand-to-hand combat.
Supplies.Lore: Not much can be said about this item.

Supplies.Name: Battered round shield
Supplies.Description: A shield used by infantry troops. More specifically, this is a concave shield fitted with enarmes on the inside, one adjustable by a buckle, to be attached to the forearm, and the other fixed as a grip for the left hand. Somewhere between 45 to 55 cm, this shield is made from two very thin layers of flat wooden boards, with the grain of each layer at right angles to the other. They are fixed together with small wooden pegs, forming plywood. The front is covered with a tough cowhide, which is often decorated with embossed stylish patterns. This is fixed to the wood with many brass, or in some cases, silver, nails, as occasionally brass plates are also fixed to the face for strength and decoration. Round shields generally have center bosses of brass.
Supplies.Lore: Not much can be said about this item.

Supplies.Name: Conventional kettle hat
Supplies.Description: A type of helmet usually made of iron or steel in the shape of a brimmed hat. Of a simple design requiring less time and skill to produce than some other helmet types, it is relatively inexpensive. It is worn most commonly by infantry, and is common all over the Southern parts of the Dragonmaw continent.
Supplies.Lore: Not much can be said about this item.

Supplies.Name: Normal luivalron
Supplies.Description: A large bladed, single-edged messer-like weapon of elvish origin, more commonly worn by the elves of the Three Seas continent. This sword type varies in size, from a one-handed to that of dagger.
Supplies.Lore: Not much can be said about this item.

Supplies.Name: Somewhat useful for desired purpose longsword
Supplies.Description: A longsword (also spelled as long sword or long-sword) is a type of Danarian sword characterized as having a cruciform hilt with a grip for primarily two-handed use (around 16 to 28 cm), a straight double-edged blade of around 85 to 110 cm, and weighing approximately 1 to 1.5 kg. This well balanced sword has a multitude of roles in combat, as the martial prowess of knights from human kingdoms has proven many times.
Supplies.Lore: Not much can be said about this item.
